summary:
- Dr. Rogers is interested in the people who come to this hospital and wants to learn how they can be of more help to them in the future. Dr. Rogers asks the patient to tell him about herself and her situation.
- Speaker B tells the interviewer that she and her husband went to California with her little boy. They had a good time and got along better when they were just by themselves. But her mother talked behind her own brother's back.
- Speaker B tells the doctor that she was scared to ride in her father's car during the storm because her father was drunk and had his arm around her. She feels that she wants to be attractive to other men even though she is married.
